'''''Religion on the Line''''' is the name of a number of local [[talk radio]] programs, where a variety of [[clergy]] members discuss religious and other topics.  On [[WABC (AM)|WABC]] in New York, it is hosted by Rabbi [[Joseph Potasnik]] and Deacon [[Kevin McCormack]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wabcradio.com/page.php?page_id=412 |title=Religion on the Line |publisher=77 WABC Radio New York |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141217030715/http://www.wabcradio.com/page.php?page_id=412 |archivedate=2014-12-17 |df= }}</ref>  On [[KCMO (AM)|KCMO]] in Kansas City, it is hosted by Reverend Robert Lee Hill, Chancellor George M. Noonan, and Rabbi Emeritus Michael Zedek.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://religionontheline.org/history.htm|title=History of the Show|publisher=Religion on the Line|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221034814/http://religionontheline.org/history.htm|archivedate=2015-02-21|df=}}</ref> On [[KABC (AM)|KABC]] in Los Angeles, it was hosted by [[Dennis Prager]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.latimes.com/keyword/religion-on-the-line-radio-program|title=Articles about Religion On The Line Radio Program |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=}}</ref>

